---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Daniel Tse and the editorial direction behind danieltse.org.">
  <section class="page-lead">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Hands-on engineering leadership, documented through proof.</h1>
    <p class="page-lead-summary">
      I care about AI systems that behave under pressure, backend services that stay legible under
      load, and cloud platforms that reduce operator drag instead of multiplying it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="copy-grid">
    <div>
      <h2>What this site is for</h2>
      <p>
        This is the canonical home for my writing and the narrative layer around the projects that
        back it up. Long-form essays live here first. Project pages exist only for work with real
        surface area, evidence, and a maintenance story.
      </p>
      <p>
        The editorial line is deliberate: practical systems thinking, benchmark caveats,
        implementation detail, and engineering judgment rather than generic trend commentary.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>What I write about</h2>
      <p>
        Expect essays on local LLMs, integration protocols, JVM and Kotlin backend work, cloud
        infrastructure, delivery pipelines, and the operational details that decide whether an
        architecture is elegant only on slides or robust in production.
      </p>
      <p>
        Notes stay shorter and more tactical. Essays expand the reasoning. Project pages show the
        shipped systems, benchmarks, and tooling choices that give the writing teeth.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
